text: Choi Hyun-suk (Korean: 최현석; born April 21, 1999) is a South Korean rapper and one of two leaders alongside Park Ji-hoon of boy group Treasure under YG Entertainment. The group made their official debut on August 7, 2020 with the lead single, "Boy". He is also known for his television appearances as a contestant on reality-survival programs Mix Nine and YG Treasure Box. ==References== Category:South Korean singers Category:1999 births Category:Living people
title: Choi Hyun-suk
